MUENCH-KREUZER CANDLE COMPANY, Inc., Plaintiff-Appellant, v. MACK MILLER CANDLE COMPANY, Defendant-Appellee. No. 154. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Oct. 4, 1933. Martin & Rendell, of Utica, N. Y. (Richard R. Martin, of Utica, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Eugene A. Thompson, of Syracuse, N. Y., for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open court.
